  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/texts/rubber-hose-realism/> ;
  schema:name "Rubber-Hose Realism: From Koko the Clown and Mickey Mouse to the Aesthetic Toolkit of the U.S. 4th Psychological Operations Group" ;
  schema:description "A genealogy of rubber-hose realism — a U.S. soft-power aesthetic running from Fleischer's Koko the Clown and Disney's Mickey Mouse to the 4th PSYOP Group's Ghosts in the Machine — that uses cartoon elasticity, infantilization, and consequence-free violence to manage audience affect." ;
